Diffusion was modeled by the fitting of a tensor at each voxel using FSL’s diffusion toolbox. Each tensor can be defined by its three principle Eigen vectors (i.e., λ1, λ2, λ3). Tensor maps were used to calculate corresponding maps of fractional anisotropy (FA; \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
